g/resource/Chinese_philosophy\"}, {\"begin\": 1518, \"end\": 1520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\", \"score\": 0.9999665057168993, \"rank\": 3.3495405017158094e-05, \"text\": \"BC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Confucius\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1427}, {\"ngram\": \"teacher\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1491}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His thoughts and teachings have profoundly influenced Chinese culture and philosophy for over two millennia.\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1565, \"end\": 1591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hinduism_in_China\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"influenced Chinese culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hinduism_in_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hinduism_in_China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His thoughts\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1534}, {\"ngram\": \"teachings\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"philosophy\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1606}, {\"ngram\": \"over two millennia\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1629}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He emphasized the importance of morality, social harmony, and proper conduct in both personal and political spheres.\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1747, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the importance\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1659}, {\"ngram\": \"morality\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \"social harmony\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1687}, {\"ngram\": \"proper conduct\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1707}, {\"ngram\": \"both personal and political spheres\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1746}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Central to his philosophy are the concepts of humanness or \\\"Ren\\\" (\\u00e4\\u00bb\\u0081), rite or \\\"Li\\\" (\\u00e7\\u00a4\\u00bc), and filial piety or \\\"Xiao\\\" (\\u00e5\\u00ad\\u009d).\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1874, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his philosophy\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1774}, {\"ngram\": \"the concepts\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1791}, {\"ngram\": \"humanness\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1804}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Ren\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1812}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e4\\u00bb\\u0081\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1818}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e5\\u00ad\\u009d\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1872}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He believed that a well-ordered society could be achieved through the cultivation of virtuous individuals who adhere to ethical principles and respect hierarchical social relationships.\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 2060, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a well-ordered society\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"the cultivation\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1956}, {\"ngram\": \"virtuous individuals\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1980}, {\"ngram\": \"ethical principles\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2013}, {\"ngram\": \"hierarchical social relationships\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The teachings of Confucius were later compiled by his disciples into the Analects, which continues to wield enormous influence in Asia today.\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2078, \"end\": 2087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Confucius\", \"score\": 0.9999999973247213, \"rank\": 2.6754147426399883e-09, \"text\": \"Confucius\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Confucius\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Confucius\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The teachings\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2074}, {\"ngram\": \"his disciples\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2124}, {\"ngram\": \"the Analects\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2142}, {\"ngram\": \"enormous influence\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2187}, {\"ngram\": \"Asia\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2195}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sports competitions are not only about competition but also about sportsmanship by displaying fairness, openness and justness,\\\" said Du Li, Chinese Olympic Champion in 10-meter air rifle.\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2338, \"end\": 2343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Du_Li\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Du Li\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Du_Li\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Du_Li\"}, {\"begin\": 2345, \"end\": 2352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_culture\", \"score\": 0.9999998656012484, \"rank\": 1.336989260167077e-07, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_culture\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_culture\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sports competitions\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2224}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2255}, {\"ngram\": \"sportsmanship\", \"from\": 2271, \"to\": 2284}, {\"ngram\": \"fairness\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2307}, {\"ngram\": \"openness\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2317}, {\"ngram\": \"justness\", \"from\": 2322, \"to\": 2330}, {\"ngram\": \"10-meter air rifle\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shared values across the times Confucianism and Olympic values both advocate for communal harmony and social cohesion.\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2513, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Shared values\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2407}, {\"ngram\": \"the times\", \"from\": 2415, \"to\": 2424}, {\"ngram\": \"Confucianism and Olympic values\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2456}, {\"ngram\": \"communal harmony\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2491}, {\"ngram\": \"social cohesion\", \"from\": 2496, \"to\": 2511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Confucian thought, the idea of \\\"Li\\\" (\\u00e7\\u00a4\\u00bc), or ritual propriety, underscores the importance of social order and harmonious relationships.\", \"from\": 2514, \"to\": 2653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2517, \"end\": 2526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Confucius\", \"score\": 0.9999980782168044, \"rank\": 1.9217869109334753e-06, \"text\": \"Confucian\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Confucius\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Confucius\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2544}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Li\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2551}, {\"ngram\": \"ritual propriety\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2579}, {\"ngram\": \"the importance\", \"from\": 2593, \"to\": 2607}, {\"ngram\": \"social order\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2623}, {\"ngram\": \"harmonious relationships\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2652}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Li\\\" encompasses a range of behaviors and rituals designed to promote social stability and mutual respect.\", \"from\": 2654, \"to\": 2760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2655, \"end\": 2657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithium\", \"score\": 0.9915851397303304, \"rank\": 0.008486271054641418, \"text\": \"Li\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a range\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2678}, {\"ngram\": \"behaviors\", \"from\": 2682, \"to\": 2691}, {\"ngram\": \"rituals\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2703}, {\"ngram\": \"social stability\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2740}, {\"ngram\": \"mutual respect\", \"from\": 2745, \"to\": 2759}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By adhering to \\\"Li,\\\" individuals contribute to a well-ordered society where everyone plays a part in maintaining harmony.\", \"from\": 2761, \"to\": 2882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2777, \"end\": 2779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithium\", \"score\": 0.9915851397303304, \"rank\": 0.008486271054641418, \"text\": \"Li\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2793}, {\"ngram\": \"a well-ordered society\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2830}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2845}, {\"ngram\": \"a part\", \"from\": 2852, \"to\": 2858}, {\"ngram\": \"harmony\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic values similarly promote unity and solidarity.\", \"from\": 2884, \"to\": 2942, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic values\", \"from\": 2884, \"to\": 2902}, {\"ngram\": \"unity\", \"from\": 2921, \"to\": 2926}, {\"ngram\": \"solidarity\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 2941}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics bring together athletes from around the world, fostering a sense of global community and mutual understanding.\", \"from\": 2943, \"to\": 3066, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 2943, \"to\": 2955}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2971, \"to\": 2979}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2992, \"to\": 3001}, {\"ngram\": \"a sense\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3020}, {\"ngram\": \"global community\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3040}, {\"ngram\": \"mutual understanding\", \"from\": 3045, \"to\": 3065}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Charter explicitly states that the goal of Olympism is to place sports at the service of the harmonious development of humankind, promoting a peaceful society concerned with the preservation of human dignity.\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3287, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic Charter\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3086}, {\"ngram\": \"the goal\", \"from\": 3110, \"to\": 3118}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympism\", \"from\": 3122, \"to\": 3130}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 3143, \"to\": 3149}, {\"ngram\": \"the service\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3164}, {\"ngram\": \"the harmonious development\", \"from\": 3168, \"to\": 3194}, {\"ngram\": \"humankin